    <p>In­tro­duc­ing the 2021 Hyundai Avante (right) – l onger, wider, lower and roomier. Built on a new plat­form, the car is also lighter than its key ri­vals, al­low­ing it to ac­cel­er­ate and stop faster, as well as be more fuel-ef­fi­cient.</p>
    <p>The car comes with a slew of pre­mium fea­tures, in­clud­ing wire­less phone con­nec­tiv­ity, adap­tive cruise con­trol, lane-keep­ing, rear cross-traf­fic alert, front col­li­sion avoid­ance (even when cor­ner­ing at low speeds) and re­mote en­gine start. The Elite vari­ant is priced at $106,999 and the S vari­ant at $99,999.</p>

